manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Sleek Design, Reinforced Structure TEAMGROUP has adopted a gorgeous streamlines design with multi-angular to overall outline for visual aesthetics and showcase VULCAN DDR5's unique features, delivering a sleek OC gaming memory that packs a powerful performance.

Better Cooling TEAMGROUP uses a professional-grade thermal conducting silicon to reinforce adhesion between the cooling fin and memory. The silicon also allows for incredible cooling as it transfers the heat from top to bottom rapidly, ensuring that the memory remains at the optimal operating temperature.
Supports Intel XMP3.0 for One-Click Overclocking Supports the latest Intel XMP3.0 and one-click overclocking technology; users can experience ultra-fast overclocking speeds at a single click.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 31, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great DDR5 at a great price.
reviews.reviewText: I'm using an MSI B650 Gaming Plus WIFI ATX motherboard. I put in the RAM and when I went into BIOS to set the EXPO the memory worked without issue. By the way this is my experience with this RAM so I'd recommend going to your motherboard page and looking at the QVL for their supported memory so you don't risk incompatibility problems. Not every memory kit is guarantied to work with different motherboards.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 8, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars 16 is good 32 is better!
reviews.reviewText: I have a new gamer computer system, although I am not a gamer. I am a semiprofessional photographer and after a couple of decades of experience have discovered that gamer computers have all the specs that a professional photographer requires. Plus I love the lights - lol.As you may know, ram helps speed up certain demanding software programs, however, pc’s can be very sensitive to changes in hardware, especially memory. So ideally add ram in pairs, same specs and same manufacturing sequence. You can avoid returns and bios adjustments if you add ram as identical as possible to the current ram.This is what led me to this purchase and everything is working well. Love the new speed and responsiveness.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 20, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Went From Corsair to Teamgroup
reviews.reviewText: I returned my Corsair ram for Teamgroup as it was recommended for my X670E board for compatibility and I've been a die-hard Corsair user. It broke my heart but at the end of it all I found Teamgroup T-Force to be rock solid and perform no different than Corsair at less the $$$. I will be a T-Force cheerleader from now on!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 24, 2023
reviews.reviewText: This ram is great. I bought ram from a dif brand not too long ago, and have been experiencing crashes on my PC since I’ve built it. I finally figured out months later that the RAM was faulty. I had to run a Windows Memory Diagnostic to pinpoint the issue.I suggest when you buy RAM, no matter the brand, you should run the diagnostic to ensure that there aren’t any issues with the exact sticks you got. If there’s something wrong, return it and get a different brand.This brand passed all my tests, works great. PC doesn’t crash anymore :)

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 16, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Easy RAM upgrade for gaming desktop PC
reviews.reviewText: I keep A LOT of tabs open on Chrome, and I typically have at least 7+ applications running (or three when gaming) so I needed more than my 16 GB single stick that I got with my new PC. This was my first time upgrading desktop RAM but after reading and playing PC Builder Simulator a bit I figured I'd give it a shot. I wanted RAM with a little protection and heat spreading but didn't need RGB lighting as I'd rather save that bit of electricity consumption. The 32 GB (16 GB x2) was super easy to swap in, just make sure you use the right slots and actually need DDR5 RAM, not the older and cheaper DDR4.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 8, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Headline: Reliable and efficient memory with room for transparency
reviews.reviewText: Pros:- Instant Usability: The memory kit worked perfectly right out of the box, eliminating any initial setup hassle.- Quality Design: The product features a good chassis heatsink design with clean black steel and a centered logo, offering aesthetic appeal.- ECC Memory: As confirmed multiple times by the online support representative, the product features Error Correction Code (ECC) memory.- Speed: With XMP enabled in BIOS, I am pulling the full 5200 MHz speed this memory kit offers.Cons:- Lack of Clarity: The company dodges questions regarding whether it's "M-die" or "A-die", which could be frustrating for some consumers looking for that information.Conclusion:- The TEAMGROUP T-Force Vulcan DDR5 32GB (2x16GB) 5200MHz (PC5-41600) is a plug-and-play product that delivers efficiency and reliability without any startup issues or blue screens. This memory kit is a solid choice for those seeking a hassle-free setup and high-performance memory, provided they don't mind the lack of clarity about the memory die.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on November 9, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Despite this being shipped from the USA to the UK , it actually came really quickly (within 7 days). Used Team Group Ram on my previous 2 builds and can't fault it. XMP profiles load with ease. Amazon also have a much bigger variety of this manufacturers ram for sale than you will find on the usual PC Component stores in the UK. Fast and reliable stuff going by my previous builds and i expect this to be another repeat experience. Would pick this over the other top brands any day :)

reviews.reviewTitle: Well packaged and quick delivery, new opened box but
reviews.reviewText: Good delivery partner and seller but ram itself is not that good of a quality cant push to the frequency specs and the heatsink along with thermal pad is not touching the last memory chip on either side, I guess that can be fine for normal use as the die can still dissipate heat through pcb and I dont see high temperatures on hwinfo ddr section

reviews.reviewTitle: Compre 3 Kits de este mismo modelo
reviews.reviewText: Bueno después de esta experiencia no volveré a comprar rams de esta marca, 3 Kits de rams descompuestas es increíble lo poco que funciona y lo rápido que se echan a perder solas literalmente una pésima experiencia, espero que a nadie más le pase este suceso, lo peor es que todavía no se el porqué se dañaron ya que las temperaturas eran correctas y había una buena refrigeración
